        <description>PHP has it. Java has it. Even JavaScript has it. It's time .NET joined in with support for the ICU Message Format.

How would you format "He found 1 result in 4 categories", or "She found 3 results in 1 category" without bloating your code with a billion if-statements? And when you have to translate it, then what?

How about something like:

var pattern = @"{Gender, select,
  male {He}
  female {She}
  other {They}
} found {ResultCount, plural,
   zero {no results}
   one {one result}
   other {# results}
} in {CategoryCount, plural,
   zero {0 categories}
   one {one category}
   other {# categories}
}.";

var mf = new MessageFormatter();
var result = mf.FormatMessage(pattern, new {
  Gender = "male",
  ResultsCount = 3,
  CategoriesCount = 1
});

Check the README for more information.</description>
        <summary>An implementation of the ICU MessageFormatter for .NET - write contextual UI messages with proper pluralization, and more. Works with Xamarin!</summary>
